TY  - JOUR
AB  - A blush may reveal a lie and cause great embarrassment at the moment. But in situations that require trust, there can be great advantage in being known to be a blusher. This paper develops a model in which tastes are determined endogenously for their capacity to help solve the so-called precommitment problem. The tastes that emerge are very different from those assumed in conventional models of rational choice.
